{"id": 7013, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "3", "year": "2016", "session": "16N", "subtopic": "b-7-proteins-and-enzymes", "title": "16N.3.HL.TZ0.13", "topic_id": "b", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>Amino acids are usually identified by their common names. Use section 33 of the data booklet.</p>\n</div><div class=\"question\">\n<p>Amino acids act as buffers in solution. In aspartic acid, the side chain (R group) carboxyl has p<em>K</em><sub>a</sub> = 4.0. Determine the percentage of the side chain carboxyl that will be ionized (–COO<sup>–</sup>) in a solution of aspartic acid with pH = 3.0. Use section 1 of the data booklet.</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>«–COOH <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> –COO<sup>–</sup> + H<sup>+</sup>    (–COOH = HA ; –COO<sup>–</sup> = A<sup>–</sup>)»<br/>pH = p<em>K</em><sub>a</sub> + log <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{\\left[ {{{\\rm{A}}^ - }} \\right]}}{{\\left[ {{\\rm{HA}}} \\right]}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>[</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mo>]</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>[</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mo>]</mo>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span> / 3.0 = 4.0 + log <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{\\left[ { - {\\rm{CO}}{{\\rm{O}}^ - }} \\right]}}{{\\left[ { - {\\rm{COOH}}} \\right]}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>[</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi>\n<mi mathvariant=\"n